 After many complaints about heavy noise over the weekends, Lowvelder decided to investigate. Along with TJ Maré and Ettiene Maree, the newspaper visited places of entertainment in town to monitor the noise they make. The pair are member of a CPF-task team that was established to find the source of noise pollution. READ ALSO: Coyotes one of the sources of noise pollution in the city It was found that Coyotes in Brander Street and News Café were the culprits, and that because News Café played music on their veranda, it travelled into the hills of town. Take a look at the video below to see the discoveries we made during a night on the town:  